result.execSummary:
Alfonso Santos Jr. was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Alfonso Santos Jr. was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Alfonso Santos Jr.

records.addlTxt: Defendnat Alfonso Santos appears in person in custody from Grant County Jail. Attorney Anthony Pozorski appears in person. Attorney Pozorski swears to extradition complaint. State of Texas is requesting extradition. Court explains complaint, extradition rights, and right to counsel. Defendant wishes to waive right to extradition. Defendant signs waiver. Court approves waiver.
